<p id="p0026">For each 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M54" altimg="si61.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>N</mi>
    <mo>∈</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="double-struck">N</mi>
    <mo>,</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> define the sets 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M55" altimg="si62.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mi>I</mi>
     <mi>N</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo>{</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mo>…</mo>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mi>N</mi>
     <mo>}</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M56" altimg="si63.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mover>
      <mrow>
       <mi>I</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">¯</mo>
     </mover>
     <mi>N</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
    <msub>
     <mi>I</mi>
     <mi>N</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>∪</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo>{</mo>
     <mn>0</mn>
     <mo>}</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. The present section will be devoted to provide and analyze a nonstandard finite-difference discretization of the model 
 <xref rid="eq0001" ref-type="disp-formula">(2.1)</xref>. To that end, we let 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M57" altimg="si64.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>N</mi>
    <mo>∈</mo>
    <mi mathvariant="double-struck">N</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and consider a temporal period 
 <italic>T</italic> &gt; 0. Fix a uniform partition of the temporal interval [0, 
 <italic>T</italic>] consisting of 
 <italic>N</italic> subintervals, and let 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M58" altimg="si65.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>τ</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
    <mi>T</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">/</mo>
    <mi>N</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. Define 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M59" altimg="si66.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mi>t</mi>
     <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
    <mi>n</mi>
    <mi>τ</mi>
    <mo>,</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> for each 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M60" altimg="si67.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>n</mi>
    <mo>∈</mo>
    <msub>
     <mover>
      <mrow>
       <mi>I</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">¯</mo>
     </mover>
     <mi>N</mi>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. For each 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M61" altimg="si68.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>n</mi>
    <mo>∈</mo>
    <msub>
     <mover>
      <mrow>
       <mi>I</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">¯</mo>
     </mover>
     <mi>N</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>,</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> we will employ the notations 
 <italic>S
  <sup>n</sup>, E
  <sup>n</sup>, I
  <sup>n</sup>, Q
  <sup>n</sup>
 </italic> and 
 <italic>R
  <sup>n</sup>
 </italic> to represent numerical approximations to the values of the functions 
 <italic>S, E, I, Q</italic> and 
 <italic>R</italic>, respectively, at the time 
 <italic>t
  <sub>n</sub>
 </italic>.
 <statement id="enun0005">
  <label>Definition 5</label>
  <p id="p0027">Let 
   <italic>U</italic> be any of the functions 
   <italic>S, E, I, Q</italic> or 
   <italic>R</italic>. We define
   <disp-formula id="eq0026">
    <label>(3.1)</label>
    <math id="M62" altimg="si69.svg">
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>δ</mi>
       <mi>t</mi>
      </msub>
      <msup>
       <mi>U</mi>
       <mi>n</mi>
      </msup>
      <mo linebreak="goodbreak">=</mo>
      <mfrac>
       <mrow>
        <msup>
         <mi>U</mi>
         <mrow>
          <mi>n</mi>
          <mo>+</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
         </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>−</mo>
        <msup>
         <mi>U</mi>
         <mi>n</mi>
        </msup>
       </mrow>
       <mi>τ</mi>
      </mfrac>
      <mo>,</mo>
      <mspace width="1em"/>
      <mo>∀</mo>
      <mi>n</mi>
      <mo>∈</mo>
      <msub>
       <mover>
        <mrow>
         <mi>I</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy="true">¯</mo>
       </mover>
       <mrow>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mo>−</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo>.</mo>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </disp-formula>
  </p>
 </statement>
</p>
